completed.name: Assignment Name: Exploring the Advantages of Amazon's Graviton 4 Cloud Processor
completed.description:
Please research/write a report on the following topic, .5 page maximum.

You may be granted a sub-letter grade increase (A- to A0, for example) if the instructors learn something new from it!

 

Amazon has recently released a new cloud processor, Graviton 4. What makes its advertised performance so much better than the conventional x86 processor?

  • did single-thread performance increase? Why?
  • did memory bandwidth increase? how?
  • did parallelism increase? how?
  • What other factors?
  • Do you think all machines in AWS can switch to Graviton? Why or why not?

 

We are using plagiarism detection using turnitin.
completed.sunmmary:
Rephrased Question: Please research and write a report on the performance differences between Amazon's Graviton 4 cloud processor and the conventional x86 processor. What factors contribute to Graviton 4's superior performance, including single-thread performance, memory bandwidth, and parallelism? Additionally, discuss whether all machines in AWS can potentially switch to Graviton and provide reasons for your answer.

HTML Links:
- https://instructure-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/account_44070000000000001/attachments/23788140/canvas_mobile.js
completed.one_line_summary: Summary: Investigating the performance improvements of Amazon's new cloud processor, Graviton 4, compared to conventional x86 processors.

completed.description:
Please form project teams (of 3 students) and submit your team information. 

Note:

1) This is a group assignment. FIRST, each team should add members to a group - click on People, and under a Project Teams tab, pick an empty group and add all 3 members to the group). Initially there are 75 empty groups; find an empty group and add all team members to it.

2) When submitting the assignment, only one member needs to submit the assignment (for the entire team). All team members will receive the same score.

 

The submission is a text entry. Please submit group number followed by names of team members, one per line (see below). If the team has 2 members, omit the last line.

 

group number

member1_Last_Name, member1_First_Name, member1_netID, member1_UCID#

member2_Last_Name, member2_First_Name, member2_netID, member2_UCID#

member3_Last_Name, member3_First_Name, member3_netID, member3_UCID#

 

Example:

5

Doe, Jane, djane, 12345678

Doe, John, djohn, 87654321

Doe, Bob, dbob, 98765432

We ask you to submit a final report for your final project.  Here are some instructions on the final report:

1. Your team will produce a single write-up document in PDF, approximately 4 pages long.     

2. In the last paragraph of the report, please write down the names of your team members and contributions from each member.   If you work solo, please state so.

3. In the report, please describe the problem you chose and the methods you used to address it, including which model(s) you tried, how you trained them, how you selected any parameters they might require, and how they performed on the test data. Consider including tables of performance of different approaches, or plots of performance used to perform model selection (i.e., parameters that control complexity). Within your document, please try to describe to the best of your ability who was responsible for which aspects (which learners, etc.), and how the team as a whole put the ideas together.

4. The report should be written like a typical conference paper. Do not simply copy/paste your code or results from your terminals.  Try to organize it and present it in a neat and coherent format in terms of tables and figures. 

5.  There is no presentation for your final project. We will grade it solely based on your report. 

6. The report should be submitted to gradescope.
